main event: A round object, the size of a planet, was observed in the sky over Warwick Parrish, Bermuda.
interesting points: The object did not have a tail, blink, waver, or tumble, but remained constant until it disappeared.
The object had an out of ordinary speed, appearing and disappearing quite often.
The duty officer at Kindley AFB, Bermuda reported the observation to the ATIC at Wright-Patterson AFB, Ohio.
The observation was initially concluded as possibly being a satellite or astronomical event, but with insufficient data for analysis.
The object was described as low in the southern sky until it disappeared.
sighted object: A round object, the size of a planet
witnesses: Duty officer at Kindley AFB, Bermuda
